I'm trying to use a non Pro icon within a pseudo element (:before). I've been following up the docs but it's been no use.

I'm using vue.js (including vue-fontawesome).

My vendor looks like this:

```
import Vue from 'vue'
// the component
import { FontAwesomeIcon } from '@fortawesome/vue-fontawesome'
// the library
import { library, config } from '@fortawesome/fontawesome-svg-core'
// add more icon categories as you want them, even works with pro packs
import { fas } from '@fortawesome/free-solid-svg-icons'
import { fal } from '@fortawesome/pro-light-svg-icons'
import { fab } from '@fortawesome/free-brands-svg-icons'

config.autoAddCss = false;

// asociate it to the library, if you need to add more you can separate them by a comma
library.add(fas, fal, fab);
Vue.component('font-awesome-icon', FontAwesomeIcon);
```


Doing so I can use Pro icons, including Brands, within pseudo elements just like so:

```
      &::before {
        font-family: "Font Awesome 5 Pro";
        content: "\f007";
      }
```

As I said, I can also use Brands by using `font-family: "Font Awesome 5 Brands";` but no matter what I do the Free fonts are not working. I've tried using `font-family: "Font Awesome 5 Solid";` since I'm using SVG fonts as well as the font-weight approach for web fonts - just for testing purposes.

Is there any problem with the vue plugin itself or am I just missing something?

